And it gives us the record that they went forth.

00:27:05.700 --> 00:27:06.920
What a blessing.

00:27:06.920 --> 00:27:09.180
As we get into the text, it won't be next Sunday

00:27:09.180 --> 00:27:12.059
because of our afternoon service.

00:27:12.059 --> 00:27:14.940
Though, yeah, it won't be, but verses 20 through 22,

00:27:14.940 --> 00:27:17.380
we find that the first matter of business

00:27:17.380 --> 00:27:21.300
after they got off the ark was to worship the Lord.

00:27:21.300 --> 00:27:23.800
Oh, we're reminded of how important it is to worship God.

00:27:23.800 --> 00:27:26.300
He's worthy of our worship.

00:27:26.300 --> 00:27:29.020
And we'll focus on that in our next study

00:27:29.020 --> 00:27:30.040
from the book of Genesis.

00:27:30.040 --> 00:27:32.860
But this evening, as we think about this text

00:27:32.860 --> 00:27:33.700
in chapter number eight,

00:27:33.700 --> 00:27:35.500
it's more than just a historical account

00:27:35.500 --> 00:27:39.220
of some dates and timelines with regard to what happened.

00:27:39.220 --> 00:27:40.740
There's a lesson in there for us

00:27:40.740 --> 00:27:42.940
with regard to waiting on the Lord.

00:27:42.940 --> 00:27:44.059
Maybe there's someone here this evening

00:27:44.059 --> 00:27:45.700
that needs some direction from God.

00:27:45.700 --> 00:27:47.500
Don't get ahead of God.

00:27:47.500 --> 00:27:50.700
It's so easy to get ahead of God.

00:27:50.700 --> 00:27:54.980
It's easy to just kind of do what we think we wanna do.

00:27:54.980 --> 00:27:59.820
And we've listened at times to the philosophy of the world.

00:27:59.820 --> 00:28:02.380
You're gonna make a decision, get out a sheet of paper,

00:28:02.380 --> 00:28:04.500
fold it in half, put all the pros over here

00:28:04.500 --> 00:28:05.700
and all the cons over here.

00:28:05.700 --> 00:28:07.540
We hear that type of thing,

00:28:07.540 --> 00:28:10.220
but oh, how we just need to wait on God.

00:28:10.220 --> 00:28:13.300
And it doesn't matter which side has more of the pros or cons

00:28:13.300 --> 00:28:18.300
if God gives the direction, we obey the Lord and trust Him.

00:28:18.300 --> 00:28:21.340
And this evening, Noah didn't get off the ark

00:28:21.340 --> 00:28:25.059
until God said, Noah, it's time to get off.

00:28:25.059 --> 00:28:27.140
And I'm thankful for that lesson from Genesis eight.

00:28:27.140 --> 00:28:28.140
Let's pray together.

